Tableau Online Output Connection

Push your prepared data from CRM Analytics into Tableau Online with the Tableau Online Output connector and Data Prep recipes.

How the Tableau Online Output Connector Works

The Tableau Online Output connector allows you to write the outcome of a recipe to a Tableau Online project as a .hyper file.

Enable and Add the Tableau Online Output Connector

From Setup, enter Analytics, select Analytics, and then Settings. Enable Tableau Online output connection and save your changes.

In the Data Manager, click the Connections tab. Click New Connection. Click Output. Click the connector’s icon and enter its settings.

Setting Description
Connection Name Identifies the connection.
Developer Name API name for the connection.
Description Description
Username Optional setting. User name for the Tableau Online account.
Password Optional setting. Password for your Tableau Online account.
Authentication Type The variety of authentication used for this connection.
Content URL The subpath portion of your Tableau Online server URL.
Server URL The base URL for your Tableau Online server, including the pod name.

Push Data to Tableau Online

With the Tableau Online Output Connector configured, build a Data Prep recipe that merges and transforms the data to push to Tableau Online. Add an output node and configure it to use the Tableau Online Output connector.

Keep these behaviors in mind when working with the Tableau Online output connector:

* Each output node must use a different object.
* The Free Trial version of Tableau Online isn’t supported by this connector.
* This connector requires the presence of your Tableau Online default project.
